									"patching_rect" : [ 10.0, 213.0, 253.0, 126.0 ],
									"text" : "To measure your system's input-output latency, run a cable from your computer's (or card's) output to its input. Use a physical cable (yes, copper and rubber). You may have to open the Audio status window to select your input and adjust vector sizes. It might also be necessary to boost the output volume of your computer/card. Select \"In-Out Latency Test\" from the menu and start test."
